The Safety Index offers a statewide comparison of UDOT roadways, taking into account the different traffic patterns and volumes experienced in urban and rural areas. The Safety Index is a combination of four, equally weighted safety analysis sub-scores. The Safety Index is reported on a 0 to 10 scale, with 10 representing the worst conditions

The Severe Crashes per Mile Score indicates which road segments have the highest number of total severe crashes per mile per year (2011-2013). Severe crashes are crashes  that result in a fatality or an incapacitating injury. Severe Crashes per Mile Scores are reported on a 0 to 5 scale with 5 representing the road segments with the most severe crashes per mile per year (weighted by roadway center line miles).
